* SSH Client Sample

This is a SSH Client but not a practical SSH Client.
I suppose that this helps us understand SSH Protocol.

I confirm that this works for Debian sid's sshd "SSH-2.0-OpenSSH_5.8p1 Debian-4".

* License

This software (except lib/ganymed-ssh2-*.jar) is a public domain.

* Prerequisite

1. download Ganymed SSH-2 for Java Library via http://www.ganymed.ethz.ch/ssh2/ganymed-ssh2-build210.zip.
2. unzip anymed-ssh2-build210.zip ganymed-ssh2-build210/ganymed-ssh2-build210.jar
3. mv ganymed-ssh2-build210.jar to lib directory.

* Build

use sbt(Simple Build Tool, https://github.com/harrah/xsbt/wiki).

* Usage

login sshd(localhost:22) using 'test' user (with password "password")  and execute 'ls'.

% ls ~test
a hotate

% sbt
....

> run
...
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: please run 'scala SSHClientSample [host] [port] [user] [pass] [command]'
...

> run localhost 22 test password ls
...

a
hotate

...
